-- Yankees Pitcher Pettitte to Replace Injured Buchholz on AL All-Star Squad
-- Rob Gloster
-- 2010-07-06T20:55:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/yankees-pitcher-pettitte-to-replace-injured-buchholz-on-al-all-star-squad.html

          
          
             Andy Pettitte  of the New York Yankees
will replace the injured  Clay Buchholz  as an American League
pitcher for the July 13 All-Star Game, Major League Baseball
said today in a news release.  
 Pettitte, 38, who is 10-2 with a 2.82 earned run average
this season, will be on his third All-Star team. He also was
chosen in 1996 and 2001.  
 Buchholz, 25, of the Boston Red Sox, is on the 15-day
disabled list because of a strained left hamstring.  
 Buchholz was selected by his fellow players. Pettitte was
the automatic choice to replace him since he was the highest-
ranking pitcher in player votes who didnâ€™t make the original
roster.  
